benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: GET /1.0/kb/admin/queues - Get queues entries

covered: Valid Request: Scenarios include successful retrieval with various filters and default behavior (TC01, TC02, TC03, TC04, TC05, TC10, TC12, TC19, TC23).
Empty Response: Scenarios cover no data cases (TC11, TC29).

Query Parameters: Comprehensive coverage of filters (accountId, queueName, serviceName, minDate/maxDate, withHistory, withInProcessing, withBusEvents, withNotifications) including combined/partial inputs (TC02-TC05, TC10, TC12, TC23, TC25, TC26).
Authorization: Unauthorized access (TC15) and valid authentication context setup in background (Background).

Error Handling: Invalid accountId format (TC13), Valid accountId not found (TC14), Backend/service errors including 503 (TC16), 500 (TC30), and 504 (TC19) scenarios, plus security-related inputs (TC17, TC26).
Performance/Scale: Large data volume retrieval (TC18) and timeout/transient recovery (TC27, TC20) coverage.
Regression/Backward-Compatibility: Regression test for withHistory (TC21) and backward compatibility for missing new parameters (TC22).
Documentation/Error schema: API documentation and error messaging accessibility (TC28).
gaps: Pagination: No tests explicitly verify pagination behavior (e.g., page size, page tokens, total counts) with large datasets.
Rate Limiting: No scenarios around rate limiting or throttling of concurrent requests.
Caching: No tests validating caching headers (ETag, Cache-Control) or cache invalidation.
Reservations on performance thresholds: While TC18 mentions speed, explicit measurable thresholds beyond a generic note are not defined.
recommendations: Add explicit pagination tests to verify correct page size, next/prev tokens, and total results on large datasets.
Introduce rate limiting/throttling tests to ensure proper handling under high load and repeated requests.
Add tests for caching behavior (ETag/Cache-Control headers) and cache invalidation semantics.
Consider explicit tests for combined edge cases where multiple filters return empty or very large results to validate boundary behavior.
